title: Agricultural Policy
new-page: true
is-card: true
on-arrival: agricultural_policy_timer += 6; month_actions += 1
view-if: CHP_in_government = 1 and (agriculture_minister_party = "CHP") and agricultural_policy_timer == 0
card-image: img/portraits/AliTopuz.jpg
tags: govt_affairs, cabinet
#subtitle: Issues of farmer financing, grain purchasing, and land reform.

go-to: land_reform_redirect if land_reform == 0; agriculture_menu

@land_reform_redirect

We have not yet settled on a land reform policy. We must address this first before taking action at the Ministry of Agriculture.

go-to: land_reform

@agriculture_menu

= Agricultural Policy

Turkey is largely a rural nation that depends on agricultural production. Even though we historically have had problems with connecting with our rural provinces, as a governing party we must address the needs of our farmers. Feudalism still persists in the countryside which has to be dealt with.[? if rural_policy = 0 : We have yet not agreed on a party policy on agriculture. ?]

- @koykent: Actions regarding the Köykent project.
- @regular: Actions for land reform and cooperatives.

@koykent
choose-if: land_reform == 3
unavailable-subtitle: We have not selected the Köykent project for our agricultural policy!

The Köykent, literally a fusion of the words 'town' and 'village', project proposes the concentration of small and dispersed villages into larger rural settlements where key social services and industries using agricultural resources would be concentrated. Turkish villages are currently dispersed across the most uninhabitable sections of Anatolia such as mountains and hills as a persisting mark of the war-torn years of Ottoman rule. The Köykent Project is a necessary milestone in the path towards providing livelihoods on modern standards for our Turkish villagery, forgotten by authorities supposed to develop and foster them for ages.  
- @begin: Begin the rural concentration efforts.
- @spread: Spread the Köykent settlements across Anatolia.
- @yatirim: Increase funding for the Köykent settlements.
- @agriculture_menu: Go back to the agricultural menu.

@begin
subtitle: -1 budget. We will begin our efforts by assigning a preliminary Köykent for each few villages and preparing the infrastructure for social services and workshops.
choose-if: koykent_progress == 0 and budget >= 1
unavailable-subtitle: [? if koykent_progress > 0 : We have already begun Köykent formations! ?] [? if budget < 1 : We don't have enough budget! ?]
on-arrival: koykent_progress += 1; budget -= 1; rural_chp += 3; z_relation -= 5; CGP_relation -= 5; DP_relation -= 5; MSP_relation -= 5

We begin crafting the plans for how we shall approach the distribution of social services and which industry should be promoted in which region. The Turkish villager has been chained to poverty and reaction for ages; we will make sure this era is over once and for all.

Our efforts upset the right wing parties of course, since their political existence relies on the ignorance and backwardness of the people.

@spread
subtitle: -3 budget. We shall continue our efforts and begin the construction of Köykent settlements on a large scale.
choose-if: koykent_progress == 1 and budget >= 3 and spreadd == 0
unavailable-subtitle: [? if koykent_progress < 1 : We have already begun popularizing Köykents! ?] [? if budget < 3 : We don't have enough budget! ?] [? if spreadd == 1 : We have already begun spreading Köykent settlements! ?]
on-arrival: koykent_progress += 1; budget -= 3; rural_chp += 6; z_relation -= 5; CGP_relation -= 5; DP_relation -= 5; MSP_relation -= 5; growth_modifier += 0.2; unemployment_modifier -= 0.4; inflation_modifier += 0.8; spreadd += 1

The Köykent programme is popularized across Anatolia and serious funds are diverted towards rural transformation.

@yatirim
subtitle: -1 budget. 
choose-if: spreadd == 1 and yatirimm <= 2 and budget >= 1
unavailable-subtitle: [? if spreadd == 0 : We have to complete the framework of the programme first! ?] [? if budget < 1 : We don't have enough budget! ?] [? if yatirimm == 3 : We have invested enough funds for the continuation of the project. ?]
on-arrival: koykent_progress += 1; budget -= 1; rural_chp += 2; z_relation -= 5; DP_relation -= 5; CGP_relation -= 5; MSP_relation -= 5; growth_modifier += 0.5; unemployment_modifier -= 1; inflation_modifier += 2; yatirimm += 1

@regular

- @landreform: Purchase and redistribute land.
- @cooperative: Support cooperative formation. 
- @east: Support agriculture in the East with special subsidies. 
- @hashas: Re-legalize Poppy cultivation. 

@landreform
subtitle: -1 budget.
choose-if: land_reform > 1 and budget >= 1 and landreform_done <= 2
unavailable-subtitle: [? if budget < 1 : We don't have enough budget! ?][? if land_reform == 0 : We haven't picked a land reform policy yet! ?][? if land_reform == 1 : Land Reform is not in our agricultural policy. ?][? if landreform_done >= 3 : We have already carried out our land reform program to the full extent. ?]
on-arrival: budget -= 1; unemployment_modifier -= 0.5; growth_modifier += 0.4; rural_chp += 4; z_relation -= 5; DP_relation -= 5; MSP_relation -= 5; landreform_done += 1

We use the ministry to purchase and redistribute agricultural land among our farmers and rural citizens. The rural population welcomes these measures, while the right-wing parties are predictably hostile.

@cooperative
subtitle: Support cooperative formation.
choose-if: cooperative_done <= 2
unavailable-subtitle: [? if cooperative_done >= 3 : We have already done all we can to support cooperative formation. ?]
on-arrival: growth_modifier += 0.3; inflation_modifier -= 0.5; rural_chp += 3; cooperative_done += 1

By supporting the formation of agricultural cooperatives, we help small farmers pool their resources, access better credit, and bring their goods to market more efficiently. The countryside becomes more productive and prices are stabilized.

@east
subtitle: -1 budget.
choose-if: budget >= 1 and east_agri_done <= 2
unavailable-subtitle: [? if budget < 1 : We don't have enough budget! ?][? if east_agri_done >= 3 : We have already implemented our eastern agricultural support program to its full extent. ?]
on-arrival: budget -= 1; kurdish_radicalism -= 0.05; kurds_chp += 3; alevis_chp += 2; inflation_modifier += 0.5; growth_modifier += 0.3; east_agri_done += 1

We direct special subsidies toward eastern agricultural regions, helping develop farming communities in Anatolia's east. Economic development eases grievances and reduces the appeal of radical movements among the Kurdish and Alevi populations.

@hashas
subtitle: +1 budget.
choose-if: hashas_done == 0 and poppy_harvestation == 0
unavailable-subtitle: [? if hashas_done == 1 : We have already re-legalized poppy cultivation. ?] [? if poppy_harvestation == 1 : Poppy cultivation is currently legal. ?]
on-arrival: budget += 1; rural_chp += 3; west_relation -= 5; hashas_done = 1

We overturn the ban on poppy cultivation, allowing Turkish farmers to once again grow this traditional and profitable crop. Western governments express their displeasure, but our rural constituents welcome the decision.
